The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Thursday, May 13, 2004 				 Body dug up 
Kharagpur, May 12: Police today exhumed the body of 45-year-old B. Gidhle, a school principal, after his father complained he was poisoned by his wife. The body was sent for post-mortem, says our correspondent. 																								Gidhle, who ran an English-medium school at Salua, about 135 km from Calcutta, apparently died in his sleep on May 9. A doctor called by his wife wrote in the death certificate that he had suffered a heart attack in his sleep. Subsequently Gidhle was buried and his family informed in Andhra Pradesh. 																								Gidhles father G.K. Ratnaraju arrived the next day and lodged a complaint alleging that his son had been poisoned by his wife Sikha to grab his property. 
